hopobject.body: Could I borrow your phone, please? lautrepharmacie.com Drive a new BMW 3-series and you’ll start to see where the Mondeo is lagging behind. But that’s a fight that Ford lost a long time ago, not to mention one it didn’t intend to get into in the first place. Think instead of the Graphite as a rival to the new Skoda Octavia and it makes much more sense. While the Skoda has a more modern interior and cleaner, greener engines, the Mondeo remains the superior driver’s car. If only the rest of us had aged so well in the last 20 years.
